"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"[Originally Posted](https://glennsorrentino.com/articles/firewall.html) June 20, 2021\\n\\nModern phone cameras are amazing. Shallow depth of field, wide-angle, nighttime photography... ðŸ¤¤ For CalyxOS users, the camera that ships by default isn't the camera that you'd find on stock Android. Users that want the most up-to-date Google Camera app will need to download it from APKMirror.\\n\\n![Demo of limiting the internet access of Google Camera](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/R-2OD3PhO3PZJlb10jJiL.gif?height=862&width=400)\\n\\nFor people concerned about the privacy impacts of Google gathering metadata about their photos, the team at The Calyx Institute recently shipped the Datura Firewall, an app that allows users to control how individual apps connect to the internet. Options for background access, wifi, mobile, and VPN data are all controllable by the user. So you can now benefit from the Google Camera features without sending any information back to Google!\\n\\nAfter downloading and installing the app, go to the Firewall app and search for \\\"camera\\\". You can turn off all connectivity with the top toggle, or you can open the accordion for more granular options.\\n\\nQuestions? Find me on Twitter at [@glennsorrentino](https://twitter.com/glennsorrentino).\",\"timestamp\":1637778218,\"title\":\"A Private Google Camera with CalyxOS & Datura Firewall\"},\"digest\":\"FduWNkKawKxF-e41Kxyhz-nF3wDSJBGQXAmKN6CNxjk\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xf4A3BBB8560D149C116d67CA5917A186cc13Fe30\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"vWlImahoGYV67vw7XX_VucRpo5RT47X35ofZ0thFCEs\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"rw6eBnmJo5znIw_IhL7GMo3KW4ULPM4BecOGXXtq2_c\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"RQR-D39At6nqDy2s9GWzQCedqFrkOIgVm5cjx4D8lw1gpo8W8OorpCjkUQTxKPakd7tgTxWOFkmjhoR9z2s29Q\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xebdc05550e7fcc4910ea495855552fb90e42e319474dac78eeabda8b8